{{Infobox language |name=Bekais |nativename= |states=[[Indonesia]], [[East Timor]] |speakers=2,000 |dateprefix=ca.&nbsp; |date=2006 |ref=<ref>Cunningham, Ingram, & Sumbuk, 2006. ''Language Diversity in the Pacific: Endangerment And Survival'', p. 122</ref> |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] (MP) |fam3=[[Nuclear Malayo-Polynesian languages|Nuclear MP]] |fam4=([[Central–Eastern Malayo-Polynesian languages|Central–Eastern]]) |fam5=[[Timor–Babar languages|Timor–Babar]] |fam6=Tetumic |iso3=none |glotto=none |map=Bekais.png |mapcaption=Distribution of Bekais in East Timor (West Timor not shown) }}
'''Bekais''' is a language spoken on the border of [[East Timor|East]] and [[West Timor]] that is closely related to [[Tetun language|Tetun]].<ref>Hull, Geoffrey. 1998. "The basic lexical affinities of Timor's Austronesian languages: a preliminary investigation." ''Studies in Languages and Cultures of East Timor'' 1:97-202.</ref>
