{{Refimprove|date=March 2010}} {{Infobox ethnic group |group=Greeks in Norway |population=1,671 (2009)<ref name="StatNor09"/> |popplace=[[Bergen]], [[Oslo]] |languages=[[Norwegian language|Norwegian]], [[Greek language|Greek]] |religions=[[Greek Orthodox Church]] |related-c=[[Greek diaspora]] }} '''Greeks in Norway''' form one of the country's smaller [[Immigration to Norway|immigrant groups]].
The [[Greeks|Greek]] community in [[Norway]] consisted of 1,671<ref name="StatNor09">{{cite web |url=http://www.ssb.no/english/subjects/02/01/10/innvbef_en/tab-2009-04-30-05-en.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20111112103850/http://www.ssb.no/english/subjects/02/01/10/innvbef_en/tab-2009-04-30-05-en.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2011-11-12 |title=Persons with immigrant background by immigration category, country background and sex. 1 January 2009 |accessdate=2010-03-11 |quote= |publisher=Statistics Norway }} </ref> individuals in 2009, up from 1,572<ref name="StatNor08">{{cite web |url=http://www.ssb.no/innvbef_en/arkiv/tab-2008-04-29-05-en.html |title=Persons with immigrant background by immigration category, country background and sex. 1 January 2008 |accessdate=2010-03-11 |publisher=Statistics Norway }}</ref> in 2008. As of 2009, 673 are immigrants, 41 were born in Norway to two immigrant parents, and 809 were born in Norway to an immigrant parent. The majority are established in [[Bergen]] and [[Oslo]]. There are very few [[Greeks]] in [[Norway]] who are married to other [[Greeks]].{{citation needed|date=April 2010}}
==Language== 11 pupils in Norwegian primary and lower secondary schools speak [[Greek language|Greek]] as their primary language. Most of them live in [[Bergen]].
