{{Infobox language |name=Koch |nativename= |states=[[India]] , [[Nepal]] & [[Bangladesh]] |speakers= 36,434 |date= 2011 |ref= <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/Census_Data_2001/Census_Data_Online/Language/Statement1.aspx |title=Abstract of Speakers' Strength of Languages and Mother Tongues - 2001 |publisher=Go |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014133158/http://www.censusindia.gov.in:80/Census_Data_2001/Census_Data_Online/Language/Statement1.aspx |archive-date=14 October 2013}}</ref> |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Sal languages|Brahmaputran]] |fam3=[[Bodo–Garo languages|Bodo-Garo]] |fam4=[[Koch languages|Koch]] |iso3=kdq |glotto=koch1250 |glottorefname=Koch }}
'''Koch''' is a [[Sino-Tibetan languages|Sino-Tibetan language]] spoken by the [[Koch people]] of [[Republic of India]] and [[Koch people|Koch]] people in [[Nepal]], [[Bhutan]] and [[Bangladesh]].
==Geographical distribution== Koch is spoken in:
*[[West Garo Hills district]], [[Meghalaya]] *[[Goalpara district]] and [[Nagaon district]], [[Assam]] *[[Tripura]] *[[West Bengal]] *[[Bihar]]
