{{italic title}}
'''''MH & xmh: Email for Users & Programmers''''' is the first book in history to have been published within the [[Internet]].<ref>W. Stewart - [http://www.livinginternet.com/tabout.htm About the Living Internet] published by ''[http://www.livinginternet.com/tabout.htm Living Internet]'' [Retrieved 2015-08-04]</ref>

The book was written by  Jerry Peek and published online during the month of June, 1996,  the contents are advice on how to use the [[email]] [[Command (computing)|commands]] which are part of the [[MH Message Handling System|MH]] [[mail program]]  on [[Unix|Unix systems]],  including dealing with three interfaces [[xmh]], [[exmh]] and mh-e, which is used within [[GNU Emacs]]. <ref>J. Peek, W. Wohler - [http://rand-mh.sourceforge.net/book/ MH & xmh: Email for Users & Programmers]  published originally by O'Reilly & Associates, Inc 1991, 1992, 1995, {{ISBN|1-56592-093-7}} (online copy re-published (4th ed.) by the [[RAND Corporation]] & [[Sourceforge]] 2006-05-31) [Retrieved 2015-08-04]</ref><ref>T.R. Weiss - [http://www.pcadvisor.co.uk/feature/internet/20-events-that-shaped-the-internet-part-2-3272677/ ''20 events that shaped the internet, part 2''] published by [[PC Advisor]] 10 April 2011 [Retrieved 2015-08-04]</ref><ref name="Joan Stigliani">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=BW81AVydw94C&pg=PA282&lpg=PA282&dq=MH+%26+xmh:+Email+for+Users+%26+Programmers&source=bl&ots=yHX4nqZQFB&sig=uQOYUn3D5UetPR0G57mpt9OsiwE&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CFQQ6AEwCGoVChMIxdjuiryQxwIVpm7bCh0QxQch#v=onepage&q=MH%20%26%20xmh%3A%20Email%20for%20Users%20%26%20Programmers&f=false|author=J. Stigliani|title=The Computer User's Survival Guide: Staying Healthy in a High Tech World|publisher=O'Reilly Media, Inc., 1 Oct 1995, 296 pages, {{ISBN|1449399673}}|accessdate=2015-08-04}}(source: ''mail program'')</ref>

