{{for|the village in Iran|Mahamid, Iran}}

The Mahamid [[clan]] is a sub-category of the greater Sudanese-Arab [[Rizeigat]] [[tribe]] in Northern [[Darfur]], and is being led by [[Sheikh Musa Hilal]]. The Mahamid are mostly known for supplying [[forces]] to the [[Janjaweed]] [[militias]], who are—although not officially—being backed by the [[Central government|federal]] [[Islamic]] [[government]] in [[Sudan]]'s [[Capital (political)|capital]] [[Khartoum]].

[[Diffa Arabs]] tribes people of eastern [[Niger]] retain connections with the '''Mahamid''' clan, and are sometimes refer to themselves as ''Mahamid''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Niger starts mass Arab expulsions |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/6087048.stm |publisher=BBC |date=2006-10-26 }}</ref>

