{{Infobox language |name=Wakoná |nativename= |states=[[Brazil]] |region=[[Alagoas]] |extinct=? |familycolor=American |family=unclassifiable |iso3=waf |glotto=wako1235 |glottorefname=Wakoná }}
'''Wakoná''' is an extinct and unattested, presumed language of eastern Brazil. The dispersed ethnic population numbered an estimated 500 to 1,000 in 1995.
